    "user_reviews": [
      {
        "title": "Powerful compact card",
        "text": "No longer play video games so was looking for something compact, but capable. This single slot card has a low TDP of 145w and is very quiet even when ramping up. The NV encode and decode are unreal with even multiple complex 4K streams. Setup was a breeze on a headless Debian box. Though be warned, being very new I opted for manual install of both drivers and CUDA toolkit to get current support. Also being new in order to build PyTorch I am on nightly build to get access to compatible CUDA stuff which same story for ffmpeg that getting it configured for Blackwell was a process. Ultimately I am running a 750w PSU and even with a RAID 6 array the machine has held stable which wouldn't be the case with something like a 5090. I don't expect to need a new GPU for many years and my board is older so isn't capable of supporting two of these.",
        "user_name": "Nicholas",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "6 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK3pnnVFnDVGpv4s8rs8gL52MGNCI33zkDab9q9Lzzrzidbphn3mL9E4kj4XAORRr5qEgA=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc"
      },
      {
        "title": "A high end Workstation video card for Rendering models and Ray Tracing",
        "text": "Our previous video card (RTX A5000) died after several years of use (2019-2026). It served us well. The newer Pro 4000 is just as fast and capable as the A5000, maybe more so. We model in Sketchup and Revit, then render in Lumion. Looking at the Benchmark Lumion gives this card, it pegs the higher performance limit. Sorry I don't have any pix, it was a replacement and had to go into production ASAP. By the way, this is the second High End video card we have purchased from B&H, couldn't be happier with the purchase. EXCELLENT SERVICE ! ! !",
        "user_name": "James",
        "source": "bhphotovideo.com",
        "rating": 5,
        "date": "3 months ago",
        "icon": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/shsm/AGYqVK1dnWVxBg_JNlHFd4onOhGYDguOz0FbD7EIViTmO38nfG5CabFtdWYAyIsG4ItT5NfLbg=w40-h40-c0x00000000-cc",
